		<div class="make-shorter aos-init aos-animate" data-aos="fade-up">
		
						
			<h2>If one of these sounds familiar, we can help</h2>

<h3>You&#8217;ve inherited tech you don&#8217;t fully understand</h3>
<p>Maybe the original team has gone. Maybe the documentation never existed. You&#8217;ve got software running the business, and a sense that change is harder than it should be – but no clear picture of what&#8217;s actually under the hood. We&#8217;ll review what&#8217;s there and tell you what&#8217;s healthy, what&#8217;s risky, and what&#8217;s genuinely slowing you down – without the conflict of interest of also wanting to sell you a rebuild.</p>

<h3>You&#8217;re about to make a big technology call</h3>
<p>Build or buy. SaaS or bespoke. Migrate to the cloud or stay where you are. Add AI or hold back. We&#8217;ve sat in many of these conversations and can tell you what we&#8217;ve seen work, what we&#8217;ve seen fail, and what the trade-offs actually look like once the marketing is stripped away.</p>

<h3>Your team is busy but the wrong things keep shipping</h3>
<p>The developers are working hard. The roadmap looks reasonable. But the business doesn&#8217;t feel like it&#8217;s getting what it needs. We&#8217;ll look at how the team works, what&#8217;s getting in their way, and where small changes give you back time and confidence – through code review, architecture review, or process changes.</p>

<h3>Where we add value</h3>
<ul>
<li>Architecture and design review</li>
<li>Code review and quality assessment</li>
<li>Build-vs-buy and supplier evaluation</li>
<li>Cloud and data strategy</li>
<li>Software re-engineering and migration planning</li>
<li>Senior leadership advisory and workshops</li>
</ul>

<p>We&#8217;ll tell you upfront if we&#8217;re not the right fit. If you need impartial advice with total discretion, please <a href="/contact.html">get in touch</a>.</p>
			
